Using technology, find:
(i) the mean and standard deviation of $x$ and $y$;
(ii) the value of the Pearson product–moment correlation coefficient $r$.

During week 2, the participants worked on a major assignment and they each spent an additional five hours browsing the Web. For week 2, write down

(i)   the average;

(ii)   the standard deviation.

During week 3 each participant spent 5% less time browsing the Web than during week 1. For week 3, find
(i) the median;
(ii) the variance.

steps.content:
Multiply the terms in the numerator to get the total sum of heights, then divide by the total number of employees ($20$).

$$
\begin{aligned} 
\bar{x}_{combined} &= \frac{2016 + 1350}{20} \\
&= \frac{3366}{20} \\
&= 168.3 \text{ cm} 
\end{aligned}
$$
